# Responsive Scaling (normalize)

Source: `src/theme/normalize.ts`. Tokens already scaled in `src/theme/tokens/`.

## Default (always)

Use **scaled theme tokens** in Unistyles / styles:

```ts
paddingHorizontal: theme.spacing.lg
height: theme.size.button.md
fontSize: theme.typography.bodyLarge.fontSize  // via AppText variants preferred
borderRadius: theme.radius.md
width: theme.icon.md
```

Do **not** wrap tokens again: `ws(theme.spacing.lg)` ❌ double-scale.

## Escape hatch (fixed px)

When scaling must **not** apply, use `*Raw`:

```ts
borderWidth: theme.borderWidth.hairline     // always fixed
height: theme.size.switch.height           // switch geometry stays raw
padding: theme.spacingRaw.lg               // explicit fixed 16
fontSize: theme.typographyRaw.bodyLarge.fontSize
```

Use raw for: hairlines / 1px borders, switch thumb math, progress hairlines, rare fixed design-spec px.

## One-off numbers (no token)

Import helpers from `@/theme/normalize` (or `@/theme`):

| Helper | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| `ws(n)` | width, horizontal pad/margin, left/right |
| `hs(n)` | height, vertical pad/margin, top/bottom |
| `fs(n)` | fontSize, lineHeight, icon, radius |
| `sp(n)` | small/ambiguous spacing |
| `mvs(n)` | large vertical gaps (sections) |

```ts
import { ws, mvs } from '@/theme/normalize';

maxWidth: ws(320)
marginTop: mvs(48)
```

## Do not

- Hardcode layout px in styles when a token or helper exists
- Use Unistyles breakpoints for phone density (scaling handles that)
- Scale `borderWidth`, opacity, motion, zIndex, colors
- Change `theme.size.switch` / progressBar height away from raw without updating animation math

## Checklist (new UI)

- [ ] Spacing / radius / icon / sizes → `theme.*` (scaled)
- [ ] Need fixed px → `theme.*Raw` or `theme.borderWidth.*`
- [ ] One-off layout number → `ws` / `hs` / `fs` / `sp` / `mvs`
- [ ] No double-scaling
